&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to:&lt;/strong&gt; Program Director&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Level:&lt;/strong&gt; Senior Manager&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manages:&lt;/strong&gt; Program Managers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Purpose&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Manager (SM) provides senior leadership for field operations and program implementation, ensuring high-quality delivery, scalable systems, and strong people management across programs. The role owns field execution standards, operational systems, and talent development, while Program Managers retain accountability for day-to-day delivery and the Program Director retains accountability for country-level execution and strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Manager acts as the&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;bridge between strategy and execution, translating Program Director priorities into strong operational practice across teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Field Operations Leadership (Standards &amp;amp; Performance)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide senior oversight of field operations across programs, ensuring consistent implementation quality, data integrity, and adherence to operational standards.&lt;/li&gt;
